(89, 29, 1, '', '2016-07-20 19:04:33', 46, 3315, '592826778691d686733ce19494b112a15e85fc61', '{"id":29,"asset_id":"106","title":"Murky road to radicalisation","alias":"murky-road-to-radicalisation","introtext":"<p>\\u00a0<img src=\\"images\\/School\\/rab_missing_list.jpg\\" alt=\\"\\" \\/><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The youths who have gone missing over the last one and a half years belong to families of almost all backgrounds. From politician to businessman, from former civil and military officials to schoolteacher, and from private jobholder to mason and garment worker, their families are as varied as their academic credentials.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Some of them attended reputed universities at home and abroad while a section of them studied in madrasas. Some quit studies at college while others are school dropouts.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Some were professionals, holding some most sought-after jobs of engineers and doctors. A couple had active presence in the cultural field -- one was a singer and another played guitar for a rock band. One is a trained pilot.<\\/p>\\r\\n","fulltext":"\\r\\n<p>\\u00a0<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Although their whereabouts and current activities cannot be ascertained, some of them have certainly been radicalised and turned into \\u201ckilling machines\\u201d to murder innocents in the name of Islam of their own version.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The Daily Star has found this picture through its own analysis on over two dozen missing cases and reviewing the list of the 262 missing youths released by the Rapid Action Battalion on Tuesday night.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>It is difficult to say how many of them have been become terrorists as many of them might have left home for family and personal reasons.\\u00a0\\u00a0<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\u00a0<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The Police Headquarters suspect some 100 of them have militant links and are being groomed as potential militants.<\\/p>","state":1,"catid":"2","created":"2016-07-20 19:00:36","created_by":"46","created_by_alias":"","modified":"2016-07-20 19:04:33","